manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Supporting data transfer rates up to 5Gbps The S3510BMU33 Black USB 3.0 Hard Drive Enclosure with UASP lets you connect a 3.5 inch SATA III hard drive (HDD) through an available USB port. The enclosure delivers optimal performance with a USB 3.0 connection, but is backward compatible with USB 2.0/1.1 host connections as well.

Light-weight and durable aluminum enclosure With support for SATA I/II/III, and large capacity drives (tested up to 4TB) this HDD enclosure is compatible with virtually any 3.5 inch SATA hard drive, and can greatly increase the storage/backup capabilities of your computer. The USB 3.0/SATA III enclosure features high quality aluminum construction, ensuring durability.

Improved Performance with UASP UASP is supported in Windows 8, Mac OSX (10.8 or above), and Linux. In testing UASP performs with a 70% faster read speed and 40% faster write speed over traditional USB 3.0 at peak performance. At the same peak in testing UASP also shows an 80% reduction in required processor resources. Testing results were obtained using an Intel Ivy Bridge system, a UASP enabled StarTech.com enclosure.
S3510BMU33 S351BU313 Bus Type USB 3.0 USB 3.1

Applications Turn a 3.5 inch SATA Hard Drive into a UASP-supported USB 3.0 External Hard Drive - Take advantage of new laptops and desktops with USB 3.0 (UASP) connectivity. - Turn a high capacity SATA hard drive into portable, external storage. - Create a fast, portable external storage solution for desktops, laptops or netbooks. - Upgrade from a USB 2.0 drive enclosure to faster USB 3.0. - Add-on extra storage to almost any USB enabled computer system. - Backup important data to an external storage device. - Share large files between computers quickly and securely without a network. - Retrieve data from an old SATA drive, or turn the unused drive into additional external storage space. StarTech Packaging Look for StarTech Branded Packaging to ensure you are getting a genuine StarTech product. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 7, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Small profile, great speeds
reviews.reviewText: Installation of a 3.5 inch drive could not easier, and I had this up and running right away. I am getting 250MB/s write speeds on a 10TB Seagate drive. Make sure you have the correct USB 3.1 Gen 2 input on your computer. I originally had this enclosure connected to a dock that was only USB 3.0 and I was getting 40 MB/s speeds. Direct connection to the computer solved this problem.It has a helpful (but way too bright!) blue indicator light. The case does not do much to soften the sounds of the drive, so you will hear it clunking away. The case is aluminum and feels well built. As others have mentioned, there is no fan in this case to help cool the drive. Heat can cause drive failure, so this is concerning. The upright position is probably best for heat dissipation. I would not stack these things on top of each other. I've only been using it for one day of very heavy use so far.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 6, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Works great for HDDs, actually tried a couple enclosures which were not showing my 4tb WD green at all, this one was very much plug and play. The build quality is excellent, it comes with all the screws which is great and not as common as I'd hoped. Overall it does what it says and does it well. A little bit pricier than competing products but you certainly get what you pay for.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 16, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great product, built to the latest USB 3.1 Gen-2 standards
reviews.reviewText: Of the various 3.5" enclosures I've looked at, I prefer this one. It reaches very high speeds on a USB3.1 Gen-1 (USB3.0) or Gen-2 port. The case is aluminum (great for heat dissipation) and comes with a quality cable (of very sufficient length). It's easy to assemble and is very sturdy. And it has a power switch, unlike some of the pre-built units. Insert a Western Digital NAS or Black drive and you're ready to go! And it looks nice as well. I'm using a WD NAS 6TB (5400 rpm) drive in one, and a WD Black 2TB (7200 rpm) drive in another.This goes well with the StarTech PEXUSB321A 2-port USB3.1 PCIe card, but I initially tried this on a new PC with a USB3.1 port and the performance is great. With a hard drive (or even an SSD) you will not realize even close to a 10Gbps transfer rate, but the speed is impressive nonetheless.This unit does not contain a fan, so streaming, or transferring large amounts of data at once requires an external fan...not a big deal. If the unit gets hot, blow some air by it. The aluminum is doing its job. Fanless is a choice WE make. Hard Drives get hot; not the enclosure's fault! Life can occasionally be this unfair.....but the strong overcome!I use a 6" fan on the shelf containing all of my external drives. It doesn't take much to keep them cool. Just like your CPU, the aluminum heatsink draws out the heat and the fan blows it away. There will be slight audible fan noise whether internal or external. A low fan setting typically works fine.And keep in mind, with a new hard drive you must visit the Disk Management applet (Microsoft) to initialize the drive or Windows File Explorer won't see it.This enclosure also doesn't force the DLNA/DRM media restrictions of modern pre-assembled external USB and NAS drive units.REVIEWS:I read all of the Amazon negative reviews and most or all of them seem to refer to a different enclosure, not this one. This does not have an eSATA port; Is not made of plastic; YES, it gets hot (as it should) when the hard drive gets hot; You must initialize a new drive no matter where you install it; Does NOT have a fan; Should work with any SATA II/III drive; Transfers much, MUCH faster than 23-MB/s; etc.One reviewer even expected the unit to arrive WITH a hard drive inside. Another states that the drive won't spin without the USB cable connected.....could be true, drives DO spin down when not in use, but I can't figure out why anyone would want to run the drive when it's not connected to anything???!?You want it to work with systems other than Windows or Mac OS...do your homework before ordering ANY computer product.>>> This is a VERY nice unit!I recommend this to my customers. I build computer and network systems for home and small business.CLARIFICATION: The slide-in tray holding the (bottom side of) the hard drive is Plastic, but the metal top of the HDD faces the aluminum enclosure case, assisting with the transfer of heat.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 24, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent Build Quality, Fast interface - Not too Hot or Loud.
reviews.reviewText: I initially had a WD Blue 1TB 7200rpm drive in this guy, worked great, albeit kind of loud sitting on my wooden desk.I recently swapped that drive for a WD Blue 4TB 5400rpm drive for mass storage for my photo editing rig. MUCH QUIETER. I've not noticed that the drive gets too hot when writing hundreds of GB of files... so that's good.The USB 3.1 interface is fast - the UASP protocol makes a significant difference in speeds, as shown by other reviewers.Plus, this enclosure looks sick!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Caused errors on drive
reviews.reviewText: I have an internal 8TB He drive I wanted to move to an external enclosure. After installing the drive, Windows started hanging indefinitely during startup while the activity light on the enclosure would flicker constantly. The longest hang was about 15 minutes. I didn't let it finish to see how long it would go before I gave up and flipped off the power on the enclosure. As soon as I did that, Windows finished starting just fine.I moved the same drive to a different enclosure and all issues ceased. The drive is working great. Will be returning this enclosure.Final thought - I'd love for one of these enclosures to feel solid and even a little heavy. Give me real aluminum fins for cooling. This thing feels thin and cheap.Final final thought - S.M.A.R.T. did work, which was nice.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Best for baking drives
reviews.reviewText: There is absolutely no ventilation in this enclosure and it will cook your drive! The rear vents serve no purpose as the other set of vents (on the internal sled) are blocked by the outer case. And the edges of the metal exterior are sharp as a razor. I'm going to have to Swiss cheese the case components with a drill to have any hope of using this.The function is great and I like the fact that the drive is secured by screws, but the heat issue cannot be avoided. No, I would NOT recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Decent StarTech quality
reviews.reviewText: This is a good enclosure, but not a great one. I got it to house a surplus WD Black 3.5" drive which runs hot. I was hoping there would be more ventilation, and a metal-to-metal heat path from the drive to the aluminum case. The drive mounts to a plastic tray, which then slides into the metal case. I trust it will continue to work, in normal StarTech fashion, but I'll probably make sure it's in the flow of a fan if I use it extensively.BTW, the AC Infinity Multi Fans (example, https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00G059G86) are great for anything that might need a bit of help keeping cool. Highly recommended!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on December 14, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Not the cheapest SATA enclosures but value for money. Well made from metal, not plastic, and my Apple Macintosh desktop can control the power modes - they sleep or not, as I decide in the macOS settings, and power down completely when I power down the Macintosh.

Per caso l'ho comprato dopo due cocenti delusioni per avere un case adatto ad un hgst.Testato, lo alimenta bene con velocità ottime di trasferimento.All'interno l'hard disk è tenuto in posizione da 4 viti da inserire alla base, in modo che non si muova durante il trasporto. È estremamente facile da utilizzare, compatto ed in alluminio.Forse l'unica pecca è l'aerazione , poiché solo da un lato c'è una griglia per fare "respirare" l'hard disk. Tuttavia essendo alluminio si raffredda facilmente, contrariamente agli involucri fatti in plastica che diventano piccoli forni. E devo dire non ho notato aumento di temperatura (misurato con crystaldisk)Se come me avete necessità di un contenitore affidabile per hard disk, lo raccomando caldamente!Aggiornamento: dopo formattazione completa, circa 12 or do esecuzione continua, l'hard disk è rimasto ad una temperatura simile a quella di quando era collegato dentro il case, sotto i 40 gradi.Promosso a pieni voti anche per il raffreddamento
Auspacken Festplatte einschieben alles OK.Übertragungsgeschwindigkeit ist super und entspricht den Angaben !
